                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git reset --hard HEAD~1&lt;/code&gt; is &lt;b&gt;too dangerous&lt;/b&gt;! This will not just &apos;cancel last commit&apos;, but will revert repo completely back to the previous commit. So you will LOOSE all changes committed in the last commit!&lt;/span&gt;

